30/03/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Foreign Minister Ilir Meta said on Friday (28 March) that the new European Commission report on Albania would improve the country's progress in the accession process. Meta reiterated the government's commitment to strengthening the rule of law and reforming the internal affairs and justice ministries, as well as to the modernisation of institutions and economic development.
In related developments Friday, Justice Minister Spiro Peci said his ministry is devoted to widening the legislative reforms needed to fight terrorism and organised crime. Peci added that his ministry and the government as a whole are committed to legal reforms needed to better fight trafficking and money laundering. (ATA - 28/03/03)
